<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a278d99-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7301"><num value="7301">§ 7301.</num><heading> Purpose</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The purpose of this chapter is to encourage the collaborative, science-based ecosystem restoration of priority forest landscapes through a process that—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a278d9a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7301/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> encourages ecological, economic, and social sustainability;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a278d9b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7301/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> leverages local resources with national and private resources;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a278d9c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7301/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> facilitates the reduction of wildfire management costs, including through reestablishing natural fire regimes and reducing the risk of uncharacteristic wildfire; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a278d9d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7301/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><chapeau> demonstrates the degree to which—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a278d9e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7301/4/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><chapeau> various ecological restoration techniques—</chapeau><clause style="-uslm-lc:I14" class="indent3" id="id7a278d9f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7301/4/A/i"><num value="i">(i)</num><content> achieve ecological and watershed health objectives; and</content>
</clause>
<clause style="-uslm-lc:I14" class="indent3" id="id7a278da0-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7301/4/A/ii"><num value="ii">(ii)</num><content> affect wildfire activity and management costs; and</content>
</clause>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id7a278da1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s7301/4/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> the use of forest restoration byproducts can offset treatment costs while benefitting local rural economies and improving forest health.</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id7a278da2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/11/tIV/s4001">Pub. L. 111–11, title IV, § 4001</ref>, <date date="2009-03-30">Mar. 30, 2009</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/123/1141">123 Stat. 1141</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
